Local Russian hospitals to be able to transplant organs
Russian lawmakers on Wednesday adopted on first reading a law which will allow local hospitals to remove and transplant organs, something only the big hospitals have been allowed to do.
Local hospitals, which take in the majority of ill people, who need urgent treatment, cannot remove organs, "" " the law said.
Local hospitals, managed by regional authorities, are spread over the whole of Russian territory, but the most serious cases are, as things stand, then transferred to the central hospitals which are mainly in Moscow and in Russia "'s" biggest cities.
